Femora with median band of brown scaly pubescence delimited by whitish scaly pubescence intercalated with yellowish and dark-brown scaly pubescence; tibiae with white, sparse, short setae throughout and two bands of whitish scaly pubescence, intercalated with dark-brown scaly pubescence; inner protibial spur may be subequal to outer spur (
Fig. 22
) or longer and curved (
Fig. 23
).

Biological note. This species was observed (
Figs 25–26
) in the Parque Nacional do Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil . It possibly mimics a bird dropping, which we believe is a defense or a cryptic behavior.
